   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="edition"><!-- transcription goes here -->
            <ab>
               <lb n="1"/>Dis manibus s<supplied reason="lost">acrum.</supplied>
               <lb n="2"/>
               <persName>
                  <name type="praenomen" key="Caius">
                     <expan><abbr>C</abbr><ex>aio</ex></expan>
                  </name>
                  <name type="gentilicium" key="Clatius">Clatio</name>
                  <name type="cognomen" key="Rufus">Rufo</name>
               </persName> co<supplied reason="lost">niugi</supplied>
               <lb n="3"/>carissimo suo <supplied reason="lost">bene</supplied>
               <lb n="4"/>merenti d<unclear>e</unclear>
               <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">sua pecunia</supplied>
               <lb n="4"/>
               <persName>
                  <name type="gentilicium" key="Aurelia">Aur<unclear>el</unclear>
                     <supplied reason="lost">ia</supplied>
                  </name>
               </persName>
               <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">fecit.</supplied>
               <lb n="5"/>
               <gap quantity="1" unit="character" reason="illegible"/>
               <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown"/>
            </ab>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>"Sacred to the divine spirits. Aurelia made this for Caius Clatius Rufus, her most dear husband, with her own money."</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary"><!-- notes go here -->
            <p>Interpuncts appear between words, though perhaps not at the end of lines based on the
                    fragmentary remains of the first line.  Projected original surface perhaps ca.
                    30 cm long and ca. 14 cm high.  Probably the stone was meant to be cut to 1
                    Roman foot long (ca. 29.6 cm), and 1/2 Roman foot tall (ca. 14.8 cm).</p>
         </div>
